    "created_at": "2016-04-04T16:20:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-04T16:21:04Z",
    "body": "I personally haven't used used `sendSync` before.  But just as a side opinionated point.\n\nUsing synchronous execution of code to block a user from interactions with the app seems like a bad plan.  Especially when printing to PDF is involved, imagine your user has a not so modern CPU and it takes a 5-10 seconds for the PDF to render, your app is completely unresponsive for that time and might even trigger the \"Window has stopped responding\" messages in Windows.\n\nTLDR:  You should probably use the asynchronous calls and block the user interacting with certain bits of the UI yourself\n"
  },
